A veteran Nollywood actor, Jim Lawson Maduike has passed away. The thespian died on Saturday after complaining of body pains. Maduike joined the Nigerian movie industry in the early 2000s and featured in several movies. He acted in Chief Momoh, Royal Madness King, Save the Prince King, among others. Maduike was also a writer and broadcast personality. Nollywood has now lost three members in the last 15 days. Renowned movie producer, Chico Ejiro gave up the ghost on Christmas Day. This week, Yoruba actress, Folake Aremu, popularly known as Orisabunmi, also died. 